== Code ==
```scala
class SmallInt private (val value : Int)
object SmallInt {
    def apply(x : Int) = if(x < 100) Some(new SmallInt(x)) else None
}
```

== What happened ==
```scala
error: constructor SmallInt cannot be accessed in object SmallInt
```

== What expected ==

No error (works with scalac)
